}} The '1937â38 season' was Colchester United's first ever season after the
formation as a professional club from amateur predecessors Colchester Town.
United competed in the Southern Football League, finishing sixth and came second
in the Mid-Week section. The club did not enter the FA Cup, but did however win
the Southern League Cup at the first attempt.
